<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1753,1778]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Etymology</emphasis>
. The genus name is derived from the ancient Greek Kairos, personification of opportunity, shown with one lock of hair on his forehead which reminds of the male ocular area modification of the 
<typeStatus box="[1205,1253,1790,1814]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
species; gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" box="[199,1163,1861,1886]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,1861,1886]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis/Description</emphasis>
. See diagnosis and description of single known species below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1753,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,1897,1922]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Notes</emphasis>
. The recent molecular phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Eberle et al. 2018)" authorityName="Eberle" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Eberle" baseAuthorityYear="2018" box="[679,1014,1897,1922]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Pholcidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Eberle, J. &amp; Dimitrov, D. &amp; Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A." box="[804,1006,1897,1922]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="141" refId="ref37668" refString="Eberle, J., Dimitrov, D., Valdez-Mondragon, A. &amp; Huber, B. A. (2018) Microhabitat change drives diversification in pholcid spiders. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 18, 141. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 12862 - 018 - 1244 - 8" type="journal article" year="2018">
Eberle 
<emphasis box="[885,942,1897,1922]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
placed 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[1100,1193,1899,1922]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Kairona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[1100,1193,1899,1922]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Kairona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a highly supported clade together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber &amp; Carvalho, 2019" authorityName="Huber &amp; Carvalho" authorityYear="2019" box="[397,516,1934,1957]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Saciperere" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[397,516,1934,1957]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Saciperere</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(“Gen.n. Br15-45”); 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[780,1038,1933,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pisaboa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,872,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Pisaboa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[887,1038,1933,1958]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1113,1384,1933,1958]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Waunana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1218,1934,1957]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Waunana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[1233,1384,1933,1958]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber, 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. No morphological synapomorphy is known that joins these genera. They all share vertical hairs in high density on the male legs (femora and tibiae, or tibiae only) but this character is widespread among 
<taxonomicName authority="(Huber 2000)" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" baseAuthorityName="Huber" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[1093,1403,2005,2030]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Modisiminae">
Modisiminae (
<bibRefCitation author="Huber, B. A." box="[1255,1395,2005,2030]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 348" refId="ref37855" refString="Huber, B. A. (2000) New World pholcid spiders (Araneae: Pholcidae): a revision at generic level. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 254, 1 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 (2000) 254 &lt;0001: nwpsap&gt; 2.0. co; 2" type="journal article" year="2000">Huber 2000</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
